article.headline: Valparaiso 79, Chicago St 68
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Dan Oppland scored 23 points as Valparaiso defeated Chicago State 79-68 on Saturday. Oumar Sylla added 14 points for Valparaiso (11-10, 8-4 Mid-Continent Conference) and Jimmie Miles added 11. Oppland and Sylla each pulled down seven rebounds, and Ali Berdiel dished out seven assists. Joaquim Gomes blocked four shots. Craig Franklin led Chicago State (7-17, 5-5) with 18 points, and Tony Weeden added 11 points. Jeleel Akindele led the Cougars with nine rebounds and Geoff Richards had four assists to lead Chicago State. The Cougars led by 32-31 at halftime, but the Crusaders outscored Chicago State 48-36 in the second half. Valparaiso shot 52 percent from the field for the game, while Chicago State shot just under 39 percent. Chicago State did outscore Valparaiso 21-12 on points off turnovers, but Valparaiso outscored Chicago State 14-4 on fastbreak points.
